    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;necromancy&nbsp;[fear, mind-affecting, emotion];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;hunter 1, ranger 1;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;20 feet<br>\n    <strong>Area</strong>&nbsp;20-ft.-radius burst<br>\n    \n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 round/level<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Will negates;&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>With a single primal howl, you strike fear in your opponents.</p><p>Until the end of the spell's duration, you treat those affected by it as if they were your favored enemy, gaining a +2 bonus on weapon attack and damage rolls against them, and a +2 bonus on Bluff, Knowledge, Perception, Sense Motive, and Survival checks against them. If an affected creature is already one of your favored enemies, it is shaken instead. This is a mindaffecting fear effect.</p>\n</div>\n",
